        Execute a system command, consuming text output from command
        Specified by:
        execute in interface ShellExecutor
        Parameters:
        workingDir - directory to execute the command in
        outputConsumer - a Consumer that consumes standard out and standard error output from the command
        timeoutMs - maximum time to wait for the command to complete
        clearSystemEnv - By default, environment variables for the parent java process are available for the command being called. Set this to true to exclude these environment variables from the command.
        args - command and arguments to pass to the command
        Returns:
        exit code from the command
        Throws:
        IOException - if an I/O error occurs
        InterruptedException - if the command process is interrupted
